  <li> Incorporating analyses using machine learning and artificial intelligence tools when appropriate </li>
  <li>Develop independent and collaborative research projects suitable for external funding proposals</li>
  <li> Document experimental research in appropriate format for presentations, publications, and grant proposals.</li>
  <li> Assist the Principal Investigator with projects, supervising, training, and mentoring members of the laboratory.</li>

 </div>

  <li> Post-doctoral or research experience in a field relating to immunology and infectious diseases.</li>
  <li> Evidence of independent research, including publications in peer-reviewed journals and successful grant funding.</li>
  <li> Experience in supervisory and project management in an academic or biotechnology setting.</li>
  <li> Capacity to develop new research techniques and adapt to a fast-paced environment.</li>
  <li> Excellent verbal and written communication skills.</li>
 </ul>

 </div>

  <li> Development of protocols and applications for externally funded research agreements, and experience writing and submitting research grants to funding agencies.</li>
 </ul>
